This paper deals with the application of geometric analysis to machine learning and knowledge discovery, which is a topic that falls under the category of "Machine Learning" (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the intrinsic dimension of data sets, which is a concept that is closely related to data structures and algorithms, and thus could also be classified under "Data Structures and Algorithms" (cs.DS). The paper also mentions the use of formal contexts and concept lattices, which are topics that fall under "Social and Information Networks" (cs.SI) and "Systems and Control" (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the practical applications of the research, which could be classified under "Software Engineering" (cs.SE).
